implemented black 2s. changed the reverseTurnOrder function's name. implemented pickup. implemented 4cardburns (untested). added a player.getselected function. fixed removeToHand(). renamed PASS to PICKUP. started the EPICMODE state.

added EPIC Controller GameActions moved STATE change to EPICMODE and SPECTATING to setCurrentPlayerToNext fixed EPICMODE graphics added changeSTATE(PLAYING) to player after picking a bot card in EPICMODE updated playingCard so it's independent of the Idiot project

added endgame circumstances: - added endgame gameActions to the Controller - added checkRoundOver to Game - added paintGameOver to GamePanel - renamed player play() -> playSelectedCards() - fixed StartFrame to be a singleton

began implementation of inter-controller updates (#3): - added GamePanel.printEvent( - added Controller.sendEvent( and .handleEvent( - cleaned up Controller case matching - moved Controller try-catches to functions instead of handleCodes - moved the last printlns to printEvents

added chat lobby (major update): - changed from using new File() to ClassLoader so it works with .jar files - made multiple clients with a List of clientPrinters - started work on player List for initializing a game

the fullGame update: - forced locking the server before adding players to ensure synchronized playerLists - game.play is no longer playerNumber independent, works with multiple players on different games. - can now handle gameActions even if it is not your turn - - this was causing games to desynchronize because it wasnt' your turn - implemented scrapped devmode features into the command engine - gp only paints game buttons if it's your turn. - closes the listening thread when it's done listening - scrapped the adminMode for devmode commands
the endgame challenging update. - made a method to check how many people aren't spectating. apparently nobody spectates ever?
a bunch of small stuff update: - changed frames[] to gameFrames[]

the invokeLater update: - put adding players into the event dispatch thread with SwingUtilities.invokeLater. - - seemed to fix JLists not reflecting the current state of playerNames. - fixed it so that normal players only have one IdiotFrame and one GamePanel and Controller and everything. Seems to be working fine. - TODO: spectator mode.
the invokeLater update: - made validRanks a HashSet - made the eventLog prepend text - added seed-s - added remove argument mismatch catcher - TODO: /all & /seed after /lock - TODO: ready system
- added allButton - deselected cards after your turn - fixed seed-s
the Spectator update: - added SpectatorPanel class

the Spectator-fix update: - SP.handleCodes is still funny. might be sending controller stuff wrong - SP.handleEvent only does one controller. it still repaints every gamePanel tho. - made the clickPanel for SP paint names instead of player numbers, and centered names
